{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"rink-cloud-gum","description":"# WS-EVAL-EXISTING — make the migrated reviewers regression-gated\n\n## Why\n\n`verify_completion`, `review_ticket`, and `scan_spec` migrated onto the engine but\nhave NO standing eval coverage, so a prompt edit or migration is a blind cutover.\nWorse, the eval LIVE tier is currently an unwired stub (`run_eval()` raises\nNotImplementedError; deterministic scorer NAMES are inert strings with no registry\nthat executes them; the `eval-live` promptfoo step is a placeholder echo). So even the\n4 existing plan-review/code-quality specs are validated for shape but never SCORED.\n\n## What\n\nDeliver eval coverage that actually gates, for the 3 uncovered reviewers, by also\nfinishing the shared eval-execution machinery (which benefits all 7 specs). Design\naligns with 2025-26 community consensus: a cheap DETERMINISTIC gate on every PR\n(eval-discipline, zero-cost) and an expensive LLM-JUDGE tier OFF the PR critical path\n(eval-live: manual + weekly schedule, non-blocking, cached, concurrency-capped).\n\n## Scope (delivered via task children)\n\n- Phase 1: author 3 eval specs (completion-verifier, ticket-quality, spec-alignment) + offline discipline tests.\n- Phase 2: 2.1 deterministic-scorer registry + impls; 2.2 live solver w/ context-injection + repo-tool stubbing\n  (the 3 reviewers read the store + repo via tools, so they are NOT inline-feedable); 2.3 per-reviewer dataset\n  schema + validation (incl. scan_spec BATCH unit); 2.4 fixture corpus + label adjudication\n  (completion-verifier FAIL findings need source-citation fixtures); 2.5 Inspect Task glue + eval-live CI wiring.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] 3 packaged eval specs exist and are validate_eval_spec-clean with disciplined cross-family judges (gates:false), at_least(k)/epochs, coverage threshold, non-empty gold_set.\n- [ ] A deterministic-scorer registry exists; every scorer name used by all 7 specs maps to an implemented pure function; validate_scorer rejects unregistered names.\n- [ ] `run_eval()` runs live via Inspect for all specs (no longer NotImplementedError); the 3 agentic reviewers run via a context-injection solver + stubbed/fixture repo tools.\n- [ ] `eval-discipline` CI gates all 7 specs on every PR at zero API cost; offline tests assert dataset balance + non-empty gold_set (validate_eval_spec does not).\n- [ ] `eval-live` runs on workflow_dispatch + weekly schedule, non-blocking, response-cached, concurrency-capped, fork-safe; provider spend-cap guidance documented.","id":"b4af-6782-0f12-4a1d","parent_id":"6f2d-4221-26de-48cc","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS-EVAL-EXISTING: regression-gate completion-verifier/ticket-quality/spec-alignment (Phase 1+2)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782578531135292001,"uuid":"9ba82a17-269c-459a-b744-d4a0adb444bd"}